# Launch Folder

This folder is intended to support the execution of the Robotics AI pipeline.
The launch files included with the package provide functionality to bring up essential parts of the system, such as ROS 2 nodes, simulation nodes, localization, and control-related modules. This allows testing of the complete system as a coherent workflow.

## Why Launch Files Are Important
Launch files are useful because robotics systems usually depend on many nodes running at the same time.
This project includes several parts such as:

- ROS 2 communication nodes,

- localization and TF nodes,

- AI decision-making nodes,

- PX4 control nodes,

- and simulation bridge-related components.

Running these nodes separately can be complicated and confusing. So, the launch files are provided to start the required system components together.

## Role in the Project

These scripts make the process of running, testing, and demonstrating the project easier.

The launch files in this codebase serve to link the simulator, ROS 2 communication, decision logic, and PX4 flight control together.



